{{Portuguese name|da Silva|Nascimento Vinagre}} {{Infobox football biography | name= Rúben Vinagre | fullname= Rúben Gonçalo da Silva Nascimento Vinagre | birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1999|4|9|df=y}} | birth_place= [[Charneca de Caparica]], Portugal | height= {{convert|1.74|m|abbr=on}} | position= [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|Left wing-back]] | currentclub= [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | clubnumber= 29 | youthyears1= | youthclubs1= [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]] | youthyears2= 2012–2015 | youthclubs2= [[Sporting CP]] | youthyears3= 2015–2016 | youthclubs3= [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] | years1= 2016–2018 | clubs1= [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] | caps1= 0 | goals1= 0 | years2= 2017–2018 | clubs2= → [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] (loan) | caps2= 9 | goals2= 1 | years3= 2018– | clubs3= [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | caps3= 11 | goals3= 0 | nationalyears1= 2015 | nationalteam1= [[Portugal national under-16 football team|Portugal U16]] | nationalcaps1= 7 | nationalgoals1= 0 | nationalyears2= 2015–2016 | nationalteam2= [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal U17]] | nationalcaps2= 16 | nationalgoals2= 0 | nationalyears3= 2016–2017 | nationalteam3= [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal U18]] | nationalcaps3= 3 | nationalgoals3= 0 | nationalyears4= 2017– | nationalteam4= [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]] | nationalcaps4= 10 | nationalgoals4= 0 | club-update = 16:35, 22 January 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 30 June 2018 }} '''Rúben Gonçalo da Silva Nascimento Vinagre''' (born 9 April 1999) is a Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|left wing-back]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].
==Career== ===Early career=== Vinagre began his career in the academy system of [[Sporting CP]] before joining [[Ligue 1]] club [[AS Monaco FC|AS Monaco]] in summer 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ASM Foot|url=https://www.asmfoot.fr/breve-22511-Transferts-L-ASM-aurait-recrute-un-Portugais-de-16-ans.html|title=L'ASM aurait recruté un Portugais de 16 ans|date=12 June 2015|language=fr}}</ref> After spending his first season solely in the club's youth side, he signed a professional contract in June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=AS Monaco |url=http://www.asmonaco.com/en/article/bongiovanni-and-vinagre-sign-professional-terms-70757.html|title=Bongiovanni and Vinagre sign professional terms|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>
During the summer of 2016, Vinagre featured in five matches of the [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portuguese under-17 national team]]'s success at the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA European Championship]] in Azerbaijan, where they won the tournament after defeating Spain on penalties in the final.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=UEFA |url=http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2016/teams/player=250089224/index.html|title=Under 17 - Rúben Vinagre|date=May 2016}}</ref>
In August 2016, a deal was agreed for Vinagre to be loaned to [[LigaPro|Portuguese Second Division]] side [[Associação Académica de Coimbra – O.A.F.|Académica de Coimbra]] to gain experience,<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Académica de Coimbra|url=http://www.academica-oaf.pt/noticias/futebol-profissional/6281-2016-08-31-21-41-08/l|title=Rúben Vinagre e Ernest reforçam Académica|date=31 August 2016|language=pt}}</ref> but [[FIFA]], whose approval was required due to the player being under age 18, refused to sanction the deal.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Record|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/academica/detalhe/fifa-rejeita-ruben-vinagre.html|title=FIFA rejeita Rúben Vinagre|date=16 November 2016|language=pt}}</ref> After an unsuccessful appeal, Vinagre returned to his parent club in January 2017 without making any appearances for Académica.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Record|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/academica/detalhe/ruben-vinagre-regressa-ao-monaco-ja-em-janeiro.html|title=Rúben Vinagre regressa ao Monaco já em Janeiro|date=13 December 2016|language=pt}}</ref>
===Wolverhampton Wanderers=== In June 2017, Vinagre signed a new contract with Monaco due to last until summer 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=AS Monaco |url=http://liveteam-asm.com/live-asm/actus/ruben-vinagre-a-prolonge|title=Ruben Vinagre a prolongé!|date=10 June 2017|language=fr}}</ref> Shortly after, he moved on a season-long loan to English side [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for the [[2017–18 Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. season|2017–18 season]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40670846|title=Ruben Vinagre: Wolves sign Monaco defender on season-long loan|date=20 June 2017}}</ref> He made his senior debut on 8 August 2017 in an [[2017–18 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] victory against [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40785920|title=Wolves 1–0 Yeovil|date=8 August 2017}}</ref> On 30 September 2017, Vinagre scored his first goal in professional football, scoring the third goal during ''Wolves''' 4–0 win at [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41369653|title=Burton Albion 0–4 Wolverhampton Wanderers|work=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 September 2017|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>
On 30 June 2018, Vinagre joined Wolves on a permanent basis, signing a five-year-contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news |title=Wolves Sign Bonatini And Vinagre |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/20180630-wolves-sign-bonatini-and-vinagre/ |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. |date=30 June 2018}}</ref>
