{{Infobox football biography | name=Niall Ennis | fullname=Niall Nathan Michael Ennis<ref name="Retained List 2015-16">{{cite web|title=Retained List 2015-16|url=http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf|publisher=English Football League|format=PDF|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202052144/http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf|archivedate=2016-12-02|df=}}</ref> | height={{height|m=1.80}} | birth_date={{birth date and age|1999|5|20|df=y}} | birth_place=[[Wolverhampton]], England | position=[[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | clubnumber=45 | youthyears1=| youthclubs1=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | years1=2016– | clubs1=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | caps1= 0 | goals1=0 | years2=2017 | clubs2=→ [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan) | caps2=1 | goals2=0 | nationalyears1 = 2015 | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 7 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | nationalyears2 = 2016 | nationalteam2 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] | nationalcaps2 = 4 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2018 | nationalteam3 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate= 19:49, 12 August 2017 | ntupdate = 19:49, 26 July 2018 }} '''Niall Nathan Michael Ennis''' (born 20 May 1999) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].
He has represented England at under 16, 17, 18 and 19 levels.
==Career== In November 2015 he signed a three-year professional contract to come into effect after his 17th birthday.<ref>{{cite news| title=Wolves sign up young star Niall Ennis to fend off Premier League interest|publisher=Express & Star| url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2015/11/13/wolves-sign-up-young-star-niall-ennis-to-fend-off-premier-league-interest/| date=13 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title=Ennis turns pro|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C| url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/201671-ennis-turns-pro/| date=1 July 2016}}</ref> He suffered a fibula fracture in January 2016 that kept him out of action until the summer.<ref>{{cite news| title=Niall Ennis fighting to be fit for Wolves|publisher=Express & Star| url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2016/06/14/niall-ennis-fighting-to-be-fit-for-wolves/| date=14 June 2016}}</ref>
He was part of Wolves' pre-season preparations for the 2016–17 campaign (scoring twice),<ref>{{cite news| title=Great experience for Ennis|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C| url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/2016720-great-experience-for-ennis/| date=20 July 2016}}</ref> but did not make a first team appearance during the season proper after suffering another fibula fracture in November 2016.<ref>{{cite news| title=Wolves youngster Niall Ennis suffers broken leg|publisher=Express & Star| url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2016/11/28/wolves-youngster-niall-ennis-suffers-broken-leg/| date=28 November 2015}}</ref>
On 26 July 2017, he moved on a season-long loan to [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40735441 |title=Niall Ennis: Shrewsbury sign Wolves striker on season loan|date=26 July 2017|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his senior debut for the club on 8 August 2017 in a [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] defeat at [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{cite news| title=Nottingham Forest 2-1 Shrewsbury Town|publisher=BBC Sport| url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40785845| date=8 August 2017}}</ref>
On 5 September 2017, it was revealed Ennis had suffered yet another long-term injury, this time to his knee, putting him out of action for an estimated four to six months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2017/09/05/wolvess-niall-ennis-in-injury-setback/|title=Wolves's Niall Ennis in injury setback|publisher=Express & Star|date=5 September 2017}}</ref>
On 5 February 2019, Ennis made his first team début for Wolverhampton Wanderers in an [[2018–19 FA Cup#Fourth Round Proper|FA Cup fourth round replay]] against [[EFL League One]] side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]]. Ennis replaced [[Ivan Cavaleiro]] as an 88th minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]], in Wolves' 3–2 win at [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47037238|title=Wolves 3-2 Shrewsbury|work=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=5 February 2019|accessdate=5 February 2019}}</ref>
==Personal life== Ennis was born in England and is of Jamaican descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zerozero.pt/player.php?id=435722&edicao_id=113349&redirm=1|title=Niall Ennis :: Niall Ennis :: Wolverhampton|website=www.zerozero.pt}}</ref>
