{{Infobox NFL player | name = Aaron Hayden | image = | caption = | position = [[Running back]] | number = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1973|4|13|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]] | death_date = | draftyear = 1995 | draftround = 4 | draftpick = 104 | undraftedyear = | college = [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]] | teams = * [[San Diego Chargers]] (1995–1996) * [[Green Bay Packers]] (1997) * [[Philadelphia Eagles]] (1998) | statlabel1 = Rushing att-yards | statvalue1 = 215-784 | statlabel2 = [[Reception (American football)|Receptions]]-yards | statvalue2 = 8-74 | statlabel3 = [[Touchdown]]s | statvalue3 = 4 | nfl = HAY029662 | pfr = | cfl = | afl = | highlights = | HOF = | CollegeHOF = }}
'''Aaron Chautezz Hayden''' (born April 13, 1973) is a former [[running back]] in the [[National Football League]] who played for the [[San Diego Chargers]], the [[Green Bay Packers]], and the [[Philadelphia Eagles]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Packers.com - Aaron Hayden | work = Packers.com | url = http://www.packers.com/history/all_time_roster/player/hayden_aaron_1997/ | accessdate = October 5, 2008 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> Hayden was drafted in the fourth round of the [[1995 NFL Draft]] out of the [[University of Tennessee]]. He played 4 years in the NFL, and retired in 1998.<ref>{{cite web | title = Aaron Hayden Statistics | work = Pro Football Reference | url = https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/H/HaydAa00.htm | accessdate = October 5, 2008 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081011231520/http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/H/HaydAa00.htm| archivedate= October 11, 2008 | deadurl= no}}</ref>
