{{Infobox football biography | name = Michał Żyro | image = Michal_Zyro_2011.jpg | image_size = 200 | fullname = Michał Żyro<ref>{{cite web |title=EFL: Club list of registered players |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-released-and-retained-list---2016-17.pdf |publisher=English Football League |format=PDF |page=42 |date=20 May 2017 |accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref> | height = {{height|m=1.89}} | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|09|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Warsaw]], Poland | currentclub = [[Pogoń Szczecin]] | clubnumber = 19 | position = [[Winger (association football)|Winger]] | youthyears1 = 1999–2004 | youthyears2 = 2005–2009 | youthclubs1 = KS Piaseczno | youthclubs2 = [[Legia Warsaw]] | years1 = 2009–2016 | clubs1 = [[Legia Warsaw]] | caps1 = 96 | goals1 = 13 | years2 = 2016– | clubs2 = [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | caps2 = 7 | goals2 = 3 | years3 = 2018 | clubs3 = → [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] (loan) | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 3 | years4 = 2018– | clubs4 = → [[Pogoń Szczecin]] (loan) | caps4 = 2 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2010–2011 |nationalteam1 = [[Poland national under-19 football team|Poland U19]] |nationalcaps1 = 6 |nationalgoals1 = 3 | nationalyears2 = 2012–2014 |nationalteam2 = [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland U21]] |nationalcaps2 = 9 |nationalgoals2 = 1 | nationalyears3 = 2014 |nationalteam3 = [[Poland national football team|Poland]] |nationalcaps3 = 4 |nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate = 3 September 2018 | ntupdate = 3 September 2018 }} '''Michał Żyro''' (<small>Polish pronunciation:</small> {{IPAc-pl|'|m|i|ch|a|ł|-|'|ż|y|r|o}}; born 20 September 1992 in [[Warsaw]], Poland) is a Polish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Pogon Szczecin]] on loan from [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]. He has previously represented [[Legia Warsaw]] and spent time on loan at English [[EFL League One|League One]] side Charlton Athletic.
==Club career== Żyro spent five years playing in KS Piaseczno as a youth team player before joining the youth academy at [[Legia Warsaw]] at the age of 13. When he was 17, Żyro was promoted to the senior team and ultimately the first team squad. He spent six years in the senior team scoring 13 goals in 96 matches.
On 24 December, he signed a three-and-a-half year contract with [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michal Zyro: Wolves sign Legia Warsaw winger|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/35177291|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 December 2015|accessdate=26 December 2015}}</ref> He joined the club officially when the transfer window re-opened on 2 January.
He made his debut for Wolverhampton Wanderers on 9 January 2016 in an FA Cup tie against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]. On 12 January 2016, he scored his first goals for the club on his home and league debut, scoring twice in a 3–2 win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Michal Zyro nets double on home debut as in-form Wolves down Fulham|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/michal-zyro-nets-double-on-home-debut-as-in-form-wolves-down-fulham_sto5057400/story.shtml|publisher=Eurosport|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref> Żyro scored his third goal for Wolves in a 1–3 loss against [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]],<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35269833</ref> shortly afterwards, he suffered a calf injury, putting him out of the game for up to six weeks. On 6 April, shortly after returning from injury, Żyro was on the receiving end of a reckless challenge from [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]] defender [[Antony Kay]], causing multiple ligament damage and a fracture in his knee, ruling him out for up to 16 months.<ref>https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2016/01/25/breaking-news-wolves-dave-edwards-and-michal-zyro-facing-long-injury-layoffs/</ref> He finally made his return to competitive football almost 17 months later, on 23 August 2017 as a substitute in a 2–0 away win against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] in the [[EFL Cup|Carabao Cup]].<ref>{{cite news| title=Southampton 0–2 Wolves|publisher=BBC Sport| url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40944673| date=23 August 2017}}</ref>
On 22 January 2018 he joined [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] on loan.<ref>{{cite news| title=DONE DEAL : Charlton sign Polish striker on loan from Wolverhampton Wanderers|publisher=Charlton Athletic official website| url=https://www.cafc.co.uk/news/view/5a6623830c10b/done-deal-charlton-sign-polish-striker-on-loan-from-wolverhampton-wanderers| date=22 January 2018}}</ref>
On 31 August 2018 he joined [[Pogoń Szczecin]] on loan.<ref>{{cite news| title=Michał Żyro w Pogoni|publisher=90minut.pl| url=http://www.90minut.pl/news/289/news2895532-Michal-Zyro-w-Pogoni.html| date=31 August 2018}}</ref>
